description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: &lt;/strong&gt;Full-time 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Gosport&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 3 and Band 4 Rehabilitation Assistants&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for people who have experience in working within health care field and would be interested or have experience of working within a therapy service as a rehab assistant role.  Working as part of an established proactive therapy team providing rehabilitation for a diverse group of patients recovering from acute illness within in our inpatient rehab wards at both Gosport War Memorial Hospital and Petersfield Community Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts will be on a fixed term basis until the end of March 2021 initially, however there may be further opportunities after this time within our Therapy service across both inpatient and community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for motivated and enthusiastic individuals with a can do attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be an important part of our team and the NHS needs your help more than ever! This is a rewarding and varied role where you can make a difference to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will demonstrate flexibility, good communication skills, with an ability to work as a team member as well as using own initiative.  You will be provided with an induction period and there will be regular supervision and support around optimising your skills. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So if you can put the patient’s needs at the centre of what you do, love a challenge and what to be part of an outstanding team, you could be just what we are looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full and Part time roles will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome questions, please contact Charlotte Land, AHP Clinical Lead on 07788418551&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Happy to talk flexible working&lt;/strong&gt;-&lt;strong&gt; all requests for flexible and part time working will be considered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
